translated: Elmgren, Arne Frithiof, director, Norrköping, born on September 21, 1905 in Gävle to headmaster Anders E. and Alma Ström. Married in 1930 to Birgit Hallengren. Children: Bo, born in 1933, Lillemor, born in 1942, and Birgitta, born in 1945. Completed 8th grade education. Traveled to Germany, Poland, Austria in 1929 and to Denmark in 1946. Local editor in Finspång from 1927-1939, chief economist in Söderhamns-Kuriren from 1940-1941, executive director of Tryckeri A-B Norrköping (östergötl. Folkblad) since 1943. Secretary and chairman of Finspångskretsen of SSU from 1928-1934, chairman of the Östgöta district of SSU from 1934-1935, chairman of Finspångs ABF in 1934 and of Finspångs AIK from 1941-1943, member of Risinge municipal council from 1934-1940, chairman of Finspångs köpingsnd in 1943, chairman of the health committee from 1938-1940 and the police committee from 1939-1940, member of the Finspångs köpingsfullm. in 1943, the Östergötl. 1st county council from 1942-1943, the Norrköp. city council since 1946, chairman of the Norrköp. city sports and outdoor activities committee since 1945, chairman of A-B Norrköp. Idr :plats since 1945 and of Finspångs Mek. Verkst. A-B since 1945.
